<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,151,611]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,479,503]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species externally resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[701,816,478,502]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Anaceratagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis box="[701,816,478,502]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">A. robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below). However, it can be easily distinguished by the tridentate anal collar process and the tooth-like paired projections on the aedeagal shaft. This species may not be a true member of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zachvatkin Status" authorityYear="1946" box="[395,577,550,574]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Anaceratagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[395,577,550,574]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Anaceratagallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it has the inner arm of the style broad as in 
<taxonomicName authority="C.A.Viraktamath, 2011" authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[1131,1265,550,574]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nandigallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1131,1265,550,574]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Nandigallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1274,1381,551,575]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1274,1381,551,575]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(see below), but has the male pygofer more typical of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zachvatkin Status" authorityYear="1946" box="[704,886,587,611]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Anaceratagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[704,886,587,611]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Anaceratagallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
